The paper deals with vector perturbation precoding, which is a technique used in communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also mentions the use of an approximate message passing (AMP) algorithm, which is commonly used in compressed sensing, indicating a possible connection to cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses lattice reduction, which is a technique used in cryptography, suggesting a possible connection to cs.SI (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper deals with signal processing and optimization, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
